########################################################################

@NODE SYSTEM "Requirements"

   @{b}Requirements:@{ub}

      * An @{b}Amiga@{ub}.

      * You need the DiskFont.library (Version 39.3 included).

      * F-Bench should run on ALL Amigas.

@ENDNODE

########################################################################

@NODE INSTALL "Installation d'F-Base"

@{b}Installation:@{ub}


      @{b}Best Solution :@{ub}
      ----------------

      Click on @{b}INSTALLATION@{ub} Icon and all files will be
      automatically copied to the specified directory. You must
      have the INSTALLER utility to use this option.

      @{b}Alternative Solution:@{ub}
      ---------------------

      * Create a new drawer (wherever you want) for F-Base.

      * Copy these files into that drawer:

            - F-Bench                 (The Executable)
            - F-Bench_Prefs           (The Preferences File)
            - F-Bench_Francais.guide  (This Document File)
            - FInfo                   (System File)
            - FCopy                   (System File)
            - FRun                    (System File)
            - F-Bench.lang.uk         (Language File)

      Once installation is finished using either method, you may run
      F-Bench.

@ENDNODE

########################################################################

@NODE USAGE "How To Use F-Bench"

                    @{b}How To Use F-Bench :@{ub}


      @{b}Principals Gadgets@{ub}:

      VOLUMES Gadgets (DF0:, RAM:, DH0:, ...)

         Click on theses gadgets to list the Directory in the selected
   window.

      @{" Parent " LINK PARENT}

      @{" MENU " LINK MENU}


      @{b}++ The SUB-MENU 'Commands' :@{ub}

         This sub-menu is like this:

              @{"        Execute Command       ('Exec.Com')  " LINK EXECUTER}

              @{"   Delete The Selected Files  ('Delete')    " LINK EFFACER}

              @{"    Copy The Selected Files   ('Copy')      " LINK COPIER}

              @{"   Rename The selected Files  ('Rename')    " LINK RENOM}

              @{"       Select All Files       ('ALL')       " LINK TOUT}

              @{"      Deselect All Files      ('NONE')      " LINK RIEN}

              @{"      Create A Directory      ('CreateDir') " LINK CREERTIR}

              @{"   Comment The Selected Files ('Comment')   " LINK COMMENTER}

              @{"   Protect The Selected Files ('Protect')   " LINK PROTEGER}



      @{"<" LINK FLECHES}@{"  Stop  " LINK STOP}@{">" LINK FLECHES}

      @{" Author " LINK AUTEUR}


@ENDNODE

########################################################################

@NODE MENU "Menu"

    @{b}Gadget 'Menu' :@{ub}

      This Gadget allow you to Comeback in the main menu.
  With F-Bench, you can create your own menus and Gadgets. For more
  information about this, click @{" here " LINK CONFIGMENU}.

@ENDNODE

########################################################################

@NODE PARENT "Parent"

    @{b}Gadget 'PARENT' :@{ub}

      Each windows have theirs own gadgets. With this gadgets, you can
   comeback in the 'Parent Directory'.

  ex: You are in the directory "DF0:F-Bench/". Push 'PARENT' and you
  comeback under "DF0:".

@ENDNODE

########################################################################


@NODE EXECUTER "Execute a command"

    @{b}Execute a command :@{ub}

        You can execute a commande line like the WorkBench's 'Execute
  command'.



      @{"   Return To Using F-Bench Menu   " LINK USAGE}

@ENDNODE

########################################################################

@NODE EFFACER "Delete Files"

   @{b}Delete Files :@{ub}

      When you Push on this gadget, a window appears. Click 'Yes' to
  launch the Deleting... ALL the selected files will be deleted.

      You can stop the Delete fonction if you push the 'Stop' Gadget.



      @{"   Return To Using F-Bench Menu   " LINK USAGE}

@ENDNODE

########################################################################

@NODE COPIER "Copy Files"

   @{b}Copy Files :@{ub}

      This command copy the selected files from the current window to the
  other window.

      You can stop the Copy fonction if you push the 'Stop' Gadget.



      @{"   Return To Using F-Bench Menu   " LINK USAGE}


@ENDNODE

########################################################################

@NODE RENOM "Rename Files"

   @{b}Rename Files :@{ub}


      This commmand rename ALL the selected files from your current window.

      You can stop the Copy fonction if you push the 'Stop' Gadget.



      @{"   Return To Using F-Bench Menu   " LINK USAGE}

@ENDNODE

########################################################################

@NODE TOUT "Select ALL"

   @{b}Select ALL The Files :@{ub}

      This command select ALL the files in the current window.



      @{"   Return To Using F-Bench Menu   " LINK USAGE}

@ENDNODE

########################################################################

@NODE RIEN "Deselect ALL"

   @{b}Deselect ALL The Files :@{ub}

      This command deselect ALL the files in the current window.



      @{"   Return To Using F-Bench Menu   " LINK USAGE}

@ENDNODE

########################################################################

@NODE CREERTIR "Create A New Drawer"

   @{b}Create A New Drawer :@{ub}

      This gadget open a window. Enter your new drawer's name and
  click on 'Create'. A new drawer will be created.



      @{"   Return To Using F-Bench Menu   " LINK USAGE}


@ENDNODE

########################################################################

@NODE COMMENTER "Commenter un fichier"

   @{b}Comment Files :@{ub}

      This command allow you to comment ALL the selected files. The
  older comment is already in the StringGadget.



      @{"   Return To Using F-Bench Menu   " LINK USAGE}

@ENDNODE

########################################################################

@NODE PROTEGER "Protect Files"

   @{b}Protect Files :@{ub}

      This command allow you to modify the differents File Flags
  This Flags are :

      - Hide
      - Script
      - Pure
      - Archive
      - Read
      - Write
      - Execute
      - Delete



      @{"   Return To Using F-Bench Menu   " LINK USAGE}

@ENDNODE

########################################################################

@NODE STOP "Stop an operation"

   @{b}Stop a operation :@{ub}

      This Gadget allow you to Stop some particulars operations like:
  Copy, Rename, Delete, Protect...



      @{"   Return To Using F-Bench Menu   " LINK USAGE}

@ENDNODE

########################################################################

@NODE FLECHES "The 2 Arrows"

    @{b}The 2 Arrows :@{ub}

      This 2 arrows copy the window' Directory to the other window.



      @{"   Return To Using F-Bench Menu   " LINK USAGE}

@ENDNODE

########################################################################

@NODE CONFIGMENU "Configuration des menus"

   @{b}Comment configurer les menus :@{ub}

      Pour ce faire, cliquez avec le BOUTON DROIT DE LA SOURIS sur une
  case de menu vide (autre que la case 'Commandes'). Une fenetre s'ouvre
  alors vous permettant de parametrer votre 'Menu'. Choisissez si vous
  voulez que cette case soit un tiroir ou non.
      Entrez ensuite le nom de votre menu. Puis, si votre nouveau
  menu n'est pas un tiroir, entrez la ligne de commande a executer.

      Appuyez sur 'Sauver' pour garder de maniere permanente votre
  configuration.



      @{"   Retourner au menu d'utilisation   " LINK USAGE}

@ENDNODE

########################################################################

@NODE FBPREFS "Utilisation de F-Bench_Prefs"

   @{b}Mode d'emploi de F-Bench_Prefs@{ub}


      @{b}How To Use F-B Preferences:@{ub}

      This utility allows you to configure F-Base to your perference.

      It is very simple to use. Very self-explanatory. You have probably
   seen similiar preference or configuration utilities many times before.
   They are a usual part of many programs.

      @{b}WARNING:@{ub} The ASL.Library is required but is NOT included in
                   original archive. If you DO NOT have the ASL.library,
                   you will find it freely available on the AmiNET.

      The F-BPrefs must be in the same directory as F-Base. Do NOT
   put it your SYSTEM Preferences drawer. It DOES NOT Belong there.

   @{b}Basic Usage:

      @{b}Screen Font@{ub}:  Choose the Font used by the F-Base screen.
                    The size of this Font must be 8 or greater.
                    Smaller point-size fonts are not supported.

                    Default Font: Topaz/8.

      @{b}Edition Font@{ub}: Same as Screen Font.

      @{b}Screen Mode@{ub}:  Select the Screen Mode used by F-Base. The
                    size must be 640 x 200 or greater.

                    Maximum Screen Colors: 8.

                    Default Screen: PAL 640 x 256 -  8 Colors.

      @{b}File Configuration@{ub} : This function allow you to configure
                         easely the Recon Window. F-Bench support 20 file
                         format.



      @{b}NOTE@{ub}: When the Preference settings are saved, F-Bench_Prefs
            writes a file in the F-Bench directory. The name
            is F-Bench.Prefs. This is the saved configuration
            file. It will be read when F-Base is started.

@ENDNODE

